-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/britain-sweltered-through-warmest-april-on-record-u-k-s-met-office-says.html
Last month was the warmest April on
record in the U.K. dating back to 1910, the  Met Office  said.  The average temperature for the month was 10.7 degrees
Celsius (51.3 degrees Fahrenheit), eclipsing the 10.2 degrees
average of 2007, the Met Office said today in an e-mailed
 statement . Rainfall for the month was 36.77 millimeters (1.4
inches), the 11th driest April since record-keeping began 111
years ago, or 52 percent of the average for that month, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Morales in  London  at 
 amorales2@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at   landberg@bloomberg.net . 